ğŸ‘¤ Insider Threats â€” A People Problem

Insider threats are one of the biggest risks to water/ICS systems.

Types of Insider Threats
1. Negligent / Accidental

Usually due to lack of awareness

Clicking phishing emails

Misconfiguring systems

Weak passwords

2. Malicious

Intentional sabotage, revenge, or reputation damage

3. Theft

Stealing data, access, credentials, materials

4. Espionage

Selling access or intelligence to competitors, criminals, or hostile actors

Most insider threats are NOT malicious â€” they are accidental.
Which ties back to the theme:
